# Release Workflow

- Maintain separate update paths for `experimental` (testing), `paid` (paid-feature testing), and `main` (stable user path).
- Track one active working branch at a time, and default all routine commits/pushes to that active branch.
- Treat `paid` as the active branch until the user explicitly instructs a branch switch.
- After a user requests a branch switch, assume all future routine commits/pushes go to the newly selected branch until instructed otherwise.
- Push to `main` only when explicitly instructed.
- When promoting changes between branches, carry over only intended updates and preserve separation between update paths.
